{"key":"post-15370607","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15370607</id>\n<content>You're supposed to mix the ingredients and bring to field capacity moisture content.&amp;nbsp; I'd suggest roughly half verm and half coir by volume.&amp;nbsp; Once mixed and properly hydrated, load into jars and pasteurize in a pot of water as shown in either the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Horse-Manure-Substrate&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;horse manure tek video&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Casing-Layer-Preparation&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;casing mix video&lt;/a&gt;, as they're both the same.&amp;nbsp; Toss in a handful of gypsum. Around 2% by weight to the dry ingredients is the recommended amount, but it's not rocket science.&amp;nbsp; For the amount of substrate you describe, a handful will work great.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Maintain 140F/60C for 60 to 90 minutes.&amp;nbsp; Spawn when cool.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15370639</next>\n<prev>15370598</prev>\n<first>15369751</first>\n<last>15375218</last>\n<when>1321322027</when>\n<utime>11/15/11 03:53 AM</utime>\n</post>"}